00:12:48,343 --> 00:12:51,403
hanging around my neck?

260
00:12:51,480 --> 00:12:59,182
Lorenzo, I'm gonna go back
to California in 18 days.

261
00:12:59,254 --> 00:13:01,745
I want to take my money with me.

262
00:13:01,824 --> 00:13:03,883
Do you understand?

263
00:13:03,959 --> 00:13:07,019
No, do you understand?

264
00:13:07,096 --> 00:13:09,360
Yeah.

265
00:13:14,403 --> 00:13:17,099
We'll be in touch.

266
00:13:40,395 --> 00:13:43,887
[doorbell rings]

267
00:13:43,612 --> 00:13:46,445
Don't move.

268
00:13:51,520 --> 00:13:55,081
♪♪♪

269
00:13:55,157 --> 00:13:57,682
Hi, honey.

270
00:13:57,759 --> 00:14:00,751
Hi.

271
00:14:04,199 --> 00:14:07,168
Have you known Lorenzo a long time?

272
00:14:07,436 --> 00:14:08,835
No.

273
00:14:08,904 --> 00:14:10,735
How did you two meet?

274
00:14:10,806 --> 00:14:13,502
Business, strictly business.

275
00:14:13,575 --> 00:14:15,907
(Ramona) Hmm, I see.

276
00:14:15,977 --> 00:14:18,070
What sort of business are you in, Omar?

277
00:14:18,146 --> 00:14:21,547
I know his uncle.

278
00:14:21,616 --> 00:14:22,776
Oh.

279
00:14:22,851 --> 00:14:25,547
Yeah, yeah, it's all about business.

280
00:14:25,620 --> 00:14:26,848
Strictly business.

281
00:14:26,922 --> 00:14:28,617
(Ramona) I see.

282
00:14:28,690 --> 00:14:32,126
Well, you'll have to tell
me more about this business

283
00:14:32,194 --> 00:14:36,028
sometime when you aren't quite so busy.

284
00:14:36,097 --> 00:14:37,655
Can you pass the sauces please?

285
00:14:37,732 --> 00:14:39,063
Oh, sure. Which one would you like?

286
00:14:39,134 --> 00:14:41,534
All of them.

287
00:14:47,676 --> 00:14:49,610
Thank you.

288
00:14:58,487 --> 00:15:00,785
[whispering] What's the matter with you?

289
00:15:00,856 --> 00:15:02,949
What's wrong with you? Are you nuts?

290
00:15:03,024 --> 00:15:04,889
Who is this guy?

291
00:15:04,960 --> 00:15:08,760
- It's fine.
- Are you crazy?

292
00:15:08,830 --> 00:15:10,024
(Lorenzo) Omar and I go way back.

293
00:15:10,098 --> 00:15:12,862
His uncle and I, we played football

294
00:15:12,934 --> 00:15:16,028
in high school in Chicago.

295
00:15:16,104 --> 00:15:18,470
Omar needed to get away for a while.

296
00:15:18,540 --> 00:15:22,101
The war had a major impact
on him, psychologically.

297
00:15:22,177 --> 00:15:24,771
Everything's fine, uncle.

298
00:15:27,582 --> 00:15:28,810
He's been discharged for a while.

299
00:15:28,884 --> 00:15:31,045
How long has it been, 6 months?

300
00:15:31,119 --> 00:15:35,954
And he's looking for work.

301
00:15:36,024 --> 00:15:37,992
We may try him out at the agency.

302
00:15:38,059 --> 00:15:43,497
He'll need to talk more
than he does now, though.

303
00:15:43,565 --> 00:15:44,964
Maybe I'll send him around
in person to collect

304
00:15:45,033 --> 00:15:46,967
on some of the more difficult accounts.

305
00:15:47,035 --> 00:15:49,060
Hey, Omar?

306
00:15:49,137 --> 00:15:51,105
Do you like your omelet?

307
00:15:51,172 --> 00:15:52,537
(Ramona) I do. I do.

308
00:15:52,607 --> 00:15:56,543
I--you're a very good cook.

309
00:15:56,611 --> 00:15:58,545
I enjoy cooking.

310
00:15:59,247 --> 00:16:00,874
Iggy, my man.

311
00:16:00,949 --> 00:16:03,543
All right, let's go people.

312
00:16:03,618 --> 00:16:05,142
Why don't you just stay here by my desk?

313
00:16:05,220 --> 00:16:07,711
I gotta go talk to the boss.

314
00:16:07,789 --> 00:16:09,518
No, no, no. I insist.

315
00:16:09,591 --> 00:16:11,855
So do I.

316
00:16:15,697 --> 00:16:17,562
You're late. Lorenzo, where you been?

317
00:16:17,632 --> 00:16:20,795
Unexpected company.

318
00:16:20,869 --> 00:16:23,963
This is my nephew, Omar Adams.

319
00:16:24,039 --> 00:16:25,904
Pleased to meet you, Omar.

320
00:16:25,974 --> 00:16:27,737
I didn't know you had a nephew.

321
00:16:27,809 --> 00:16:30,175
Neither did I until yesterday.

322
00:16:30,245 --> 00:16:36,241
Haven't had much to do with
my brother or his wife.

323
00:16:38,687 --> 00:16:41,554
Well, come in my office.

324
00:16:48,029 --> 00:16:50,862
Well, Lorenzo, I can't tell ya
how happy I am that you're

325
00:16:50,932 --> 00:16:52,866
gonna take over for me.

326
00:16:52,934 --> 00:16:55,869
I'm feeling nauseous.

327
00:16:56,705 --> 00:16:59,868
Here, take one of these.

328
00:16:59,941 --> 00:17:01,238
What are these?

329
00:17:01,309 --> 00:17:03,004
Charcoal tablets.

330
00:17:03,078 --> 00:17:04,841
Go on, chew a couple of 'em.

331
00:17:04,913 --> 00:17:07,279
What are these gonna do?

332
00:17:07,349 --> 00:17:11,285
Looks like we're getting
a new boss for a few weeks.

333
00:17:14,222 --> 00:17:16,850
Speak for yourself.

334
00:17:18,393 --> 00:17:20,987
Can I come with you?

335
00:17:21,062 --> 00:17:23,189
You're uncle's a real comedian,
isn't he?

336
00:17:23,264 --> 00:17:25,732
Keep an eye on him for me, will ya?

337
00:17:25,800 --> 00:17:28,064
That's my job.

338
00:17:28,136 --> 00:17:30,263
Well, that does it.

339
00:17:30,338 --> 00:17:33,364
Make yourself at home,
but don't overfeed the fish.

340
00:17:40,982 --> 00:17:45,919
♪♪♪

341
00:18:14,002 --> 00:18:15,936
No luck, huh?

342
00:18:16,972 --> 00:18:19,907
Two ex-wives and my own mother.

343
00:18:21,143 --> 00:18:23,839
Why does everyone want me dead?

344
00:18:25,814 --> 00:18:28,374
How about you?

345
00:18:28,450 --> 00:18:32,011
You want me dead too?

346
00:18:32,087 --> 00:18:33,748
What are you playing there?

347
00:18:33,822 --> 00:18:35,722
Ultra Ninja Rivals.

348
00:18:35,791 --> 00:18:38,783
How you doin'?

349
00:18:38,860 --> 00:18:40,725
I'm on the final level.

350
00:18:40,796 --> 00:18:46,098
No kidding? Wow.

351
00:18:46,168 --> 00:18:50,468
You're pretty good at that.

352
00:18:50,539 --> 00:18:51,665
Yes!

353
00:18:51,740 --> 00:18:54,470
Wow, that's really impressive.

354
00:18:54,543 --> 00:18:59,810
You got quite a talent there,
kiddo, you really do.

355
00:18:59,881 --> 00:19:00,813
Huh.

356
00:19:00,882 --> 00:19:02,713
- You want to play?
- Me?

357
00:19:02,784 --> 00:19:06,015
Nah, can't teach an old dog new tricks.

358
00:19:06,087 --> 00:19:09,420
Go ahead I insist.

359
00:19:09,491 --> 00:19:12,722
Well, all right.

360
00:19:12,794 --> 00:19:16,560
You'll have to show me how
'cause I don't have a clue.

361
00:19:16,631 --> 00:19:19,725
(Omar) Okay, this is a fighting,
punching, jumping,

362
00:19:19,801 --> 00:19:21,166
all that stuff.

363
00:19:21,236 --> 00:19:25,969
This is how to change
the weapons to shoot at.

364
00:19:26,041 --> 00:19:28,202
All right,
where's the thing that blows them up?

365
00:19:28,477 --> 00:19:29,535
Where do I do that?

366
00:19:29,611 --> 00:19:31,010
That button right there.

367
00:19:31,079 --> 00:19:32,444
It's not working.

368
00:19:32,514 --> 00:19:34,812
Oh, come on.

369
00:19:34,883 --> 00:19:41,755
Well, where do--well, I--hey,
why don't we take a walk, huh?

370
00:19:41,823 --> 00:19:43,950
Get some fresh air.

371
00:19:45,861 --> 00:19:49,461
♪♪♪

372
00:19:49,593 --> 00:19:51,720
(Lorenzo)
That's Portsmouth across the way,

373
00:19:51,795 --> 00:19:55,561
and over there is the PAHC headquarters.

374
00:19:55,633 --> 00:19:56,964
Pac?

375
00:19:57,034 --> 00:19:59,468
You mean Pac-Man?
What are you talking about?

376
00:19:59,536 --> 00:20:02,232
No, PAHC, P-A-H-C.

377
00:20:02,306 --> 00:20:04,365
Protecting Animals From Human cruelty.

378
00:20:04,441 --> 00:20:05,465
Oh.

379
00:20:05,542 --> 00:20:08,477
Maybe they can help me.

380
00:20:09,613 --> 00:20:10,944
I had a dog once.

381
00:20:11,015 --> 00:20:12,539
Yeah, no kidding?

382
00:20:12,616 --> 00:20:14,516
Yeah.

383
00:20:14,585 --> 00:20:20,854
His name was Bombozzle, but
I had to leave him in Mexico.

384
00:20:20,924 --> 00:20:22,516
Really? What happened?

385
00:20:22,593 --> 00:20:27,030
Well, when my parents died,
uncle Frankie took me in,

386
00:20:27,298 --> 00:20:29,027
but he hates dogs.

387
00:20:29,300 --> 00:20:32,360
He probably keeps scorpions as pets.

388
00:20:32,436 --> 00:20:37,601
So what did you do that made
Uncle Frankie so mad at you?

389
00:20:37,675 --> 00:20:39,540
He Ioaned me money to start a restaurant

390
00:20:39,610 --> 00:20:42,773
and it went belly up.

391
00:20:42,846 --> 00:20:45,337
And I skipped town.

392
00:20:45,416 --> 00:20:46,713
Oh.

393
00:20:46,784 --> 00:20:49,776
Yup.

394
00:20:49,853 --> 00:20:51,878
I want to have a restaurant someday.

395
00:20:51,955 --> 00:20:53,388
Get out of here.

396
00:20:53,457 --> 00:20:56,051
Yeah, I do, but Uncle Frankie says

397
00:20:56,327 --> 00:20:57,726
I'm not smart enough.

398
00:20:57,795 --> 00:20:59,854
Ah, what does Uncle Frankie know?

399
00:20:59,930 --> 00:21:02,660
Uncle Frankie know's a lot.
You'd be surprised.

400
00:21:02,733 --> 00:21:05,031
You've been with Frankie
since you were a child?

401
00:21:05,102 --> 00:21:08,003
Since I was 7 years old.

402
00:21:08,072 --> 00:21:10,006
I see.

403
00:21:10,074 --> 00:21:12,338
What in the world is that?

404
00:21:12,409 --> 00:21:13,740
What?

405
00:21:13,811 --> 00:21:16,575
(Lorenzo)
What's that swimming over there?

406
00:21:16,647 --> 00:21:17,671
Where?

407
00:21:17,748 --> 00:21:19,340
I think it's one of those
little Chihuahuas.

408
00:21:19,416 --> 00:21:22,044
He must be trying to make
it to PAHC headquarters.

409
00:21:22,119 --> 00:21:23,643
What is it? I don't see it, where?

410
00:21:23,721 --> 00:21:27,623
Over there. I think it's drowning.

411
00:21:27,691 --> 00:21:28,749
Where? Where is it?

412
00:21:28,826 --> 00:21:30,760
Over there!

413
00:21:34,965 --> 00:21:37,092
[screaming] Ah!

414
00:21:40,504 --> 00:21:42,870
Ah!

415
00:21:43,774 --> 00:21:46,709
♪♪♪

416
00:21:49,446 --> 00:21:51,380
Argh!

417
00:21:55,586 --> 00:21:57,520
Argh!

418
00:21:59,590 --> 00:22:04,391
Aaarrrggghhh!

419
00:22:04,461 --> 00:22:07,396
♪♪♪

420
00:22:35,826 --> 00:22:37,760
Hey! Watch it!

421
00:22:39,163 --> 00:22:42,098
♪♪♪

422
00:23:01,985 --> 00:23:04,180
Ah!

423
00:23:08,759 --> 00:23:10,192
All I wanted to do was take a walk.

424
00:23:10,461 --> 00:23:11,928
Just clear my head.

425
00:23:11,995 --> 00:23:13,860
I trusted you!

426
00:23:13,931 --> 00:23:15,592
Don't do it, Omar.

427
00:23:15,666 --> 00:23:17,156
Your fingerprints are all
over the place,

428
00:23:17,234 --> 00:23:18,496
and my girlfriend saw you.

429
00:23:18,569 --> 00:23:21,868
She can identify you, and she will.

430
00:23:21,939 --> 00:23:23,804
You kill me and Frankie goes free.

431
00:23:23,874 --> 00:23:25,136
You think I'm stupid?

432
00:23:25,209 --> 00:23:26,574
Why would I think that?

433
00:23:26,643 --> 00:23:29,612
A lot of people think I'm stupid.

434
00:23:29,680 --> 00:23:32,114
I don't think you're stupid at all.

435
00:23:32,182 --> 00:23:34,673
Maybe misdirected a little bit,

436
00:23:34,751 --> 00:23:36,116
but definitely not stupid!

437
00:23:36,186 --> 00:23:37,551
Definitely not.

438
00:23:37,621 --> 00:23:41,955
If anything, you've got a kind heart,

439
00:23:42,025 --> 00:23:44,186
kind of a like a gentle giant.

440
00:23:44,261 --> 00:23:46,889
Very gentle, in fact.

441
00:23:46,964 --> 00:23:50,695
That's what I think. Honest.

442
00:23:50,767 --> 00:23:52,735
A lot of people say that about me.

443
00:23:52,803 --> 00:23:54,236
They do?

444
00:23:54,505 --> 00:23:56,063
Well, I still have to do this.

445
00:23:56,139 --> 00:23:57,868
Do what? No, please!

446
00:23:59,877 --> 00:24:04,814
[saxophone music playing]

447
00:24:07,818 --> 00:24:10,753
You like jazz music?

448
00:24:14,057 --> 00:24:16,525
Want to go listen?

449
00:24:19,296 --> 00:24:22,732
We'll settle this later, okay?

450
00:24:25,068 --> 00:24:27,002
Let's go.

451
00:24:30,908 --> 00:24:39,816
♪ Surrender to your plan ♪

452
00:24:44,922 --> 00:24:47,857
Don't make me hurt you.

453
00:24:49,826 --> 00:24:54,763
♪♪♪

454
00:24:55,599 --> 00:24:58,534
How you guys doin'?

455
00:25:04,841 --> 00:25:06,274
Hello gentlemen, you all here

456
00:25:06,343 --> 00:25:10,109
for the volunteer training?

457
00:25:10,180 --> 00:25:13,707
Well, let me get you to put
your names on here,

458
00:25:13,784 --> 00:25:16,719
and then I'll help
y'all find some seats.

459
00:25:17,821 --> 00:25:18,981
I'll see you later.

460
00:25:19,056 --> 00:25:20,318
See ya later, Liz.

461
00:25:20,591 --> 00:25:21,922
All right.

462
00:25:21,992 --> 00:25:23,960
Hey, you guys did a good job.

463
00:25:24,027 --> 00:25:25,654
- See you Thursday.
- All right.

464
00:25:25,729 --> 00:25:28,027
God bless you, now.

465
00:25:28,999 --> 00:25:32,162
All right, now y'all just follow me.

466
00:25:37,074 --> 00:25:40,237
I'm Pastor Kevin,
the director of the LEC,

467
00:25:40,310 --> 00:25:43,905
and I want to thank all you
volunteers for coming out.

468
00:25:43,981 --> 00:25:47,781
I don't believe it's by
accident that you're here.

469
00:25:47,851 --> 00:25:51,912
Something has stirred your
heart, and you've decided

470
00:25:51,989 --> 00:25:55,857
that life is more than just
"what's in it for me?"

471
00:25:55,926 --> 00:25:59,726
Jesus said, when we minister
to the least of those among us,

472
00:25:59,796 --> 00:26:02,162
we're ministering to him.

473
00:26:02,232 --> 00:26:04,257
And who are these people?

474
00:26:04,334 --> 00:26:07,030
Who are the least of those among us?

475
00:26:07,104 --> 00:26:09,629
Well, there are many different people.

476
00:26:09,706 --> 00:26:12,641
There's the homeless, for instance.

477
00:26:12,709 --> 00:26:14,768
And the drug addict.

478
00:26:14,845 --> 00:26:20,010
And there's the ex-con
or even the current con.

479
00:26:20,083 --> 00:26:22,847
And there's the pregnant teenager

480
00:26:22,919 --> 00:26:26,685
or the high school drop-out
or the prostitute.

481
00:26:26,757 --> 00:26:29,885
These are people that are hurting.

482
00:26:29,960 --> 00:26:33,828
These are people who need a break.

483
00:26:33,897 --> 00:26:36,127
What kind of rank
is this guy right here?

484
00:26:36,199 --> 00:26:38,190
(Pastor Kevin) That's the gospel,
my friend, sowing seeds

485
00:26:38,268 --> 00:26:40,259
into broken lives.

486
00:26:40,337 --> 00:26:42,999
(female) Well, a lot of our people
need computer skills so they

487
00:26:43,073 --> 00:26:44,734
can get entry-level jobs.

488
00:26:44,808 --> 00:26:46,799
So I hope you'll come back
and volunteer.

489
00:26:46,877 --> 00:26:49,038
- Definitely.
- Looking forward to it.

490
00:26:49,112 --> 00:26:50,977
God bless you, Tina.
God bless you, Mark.

491
00:26:51,048 --> 00:26:53,039
- God bless you, Pastor.
- Thanks for coming.

492
00:26:53,116 --> 00:26:54,913
Thanks for coming.

493
00:26:54,985 --> 00:26:56,213
You do funerals?

494
00:26:56,286 --> 00:27:00,325
- Nice piano.
- Thank you so much.

495
00:27:03,000 --> 00:27:04,126
(male)
We need to have a payment.

496
00:27:04,201 --> 00:27:06,070
What did you say?

497
00:27:07,438 --> 00:27:10,100
- All right, here we go.
- I got you covered.

498
00:27:10,174 --> 00:27:11,106
- Three points!
- That was good.

499
00:27:11,175 --> 00:27:13,109
That was good.

500
00:27:16,613 --> 00:27:21,550
♪♪♪

501
00:27:24,777 --> 00:27:27,541
Sixteen days left.

502
00:27:30,350 --> 00:27:34,616
Didn't your boss say
not to overfeed the fish?

503
00:27:34,687 --> 00:27:39,215
We all gotta go sometime.

504
00:27:39,292 --> 00:27:41,783
Big guy hates the little guy.

505
00:27:41,861 --> 00:27:43,522
C'est la vie.

506
00:27:43,596 --> 00:27:46,656
That's why the little guy needs help.

507
00:27:46,733 --> 00:27:49,497
Help from who?

508
00:27:49,569 --> 00:27:52,970
Who ever helps the little guy?

509
00:27:53,039 --> 00:27:58,272
I figured you would have learned
that lesson by now.

510
00:28:05,451 --> 00:28:08,352
Life Enrichment Center.

511
00:28:08,421 --> 00:28:12,585
Sowing seeds into broken lives.

512
00:28:18,431 --> 00:28:20,023
(Lorenzo) Not that I haven't
wandered from the straight

513
00:28:20,300 --> 00:28:21,631
and narrow sense.

514
00:28:21,701 --> 00:28:24,261
I just feel like it's time to give back.

515
00:28:24,337 --> 00:28:26,328
What does it say in the good book?

516
00:28:26,406 --> 00:28:30,809
Come unto me,
all you who are tired and weary,

517
00:28:30,877 --> 00:28:35,814
all ye huddled masses
yearning for bread.

518
00:28:37,984 --> 00:28:41,545
Well, I can't remember it right now.

519
00:28:41,621 --> 00:28:43,816
I'm not sure where that is in the Bible.

520
00:28:43,890 --> 00:28:47,883
Lorenzo, it sounds like that
could be another good book.

521
00:28:47,960 --> 00:28:50,019
Yeah, well you get my drift.

522
00:28:50,096 --> 00:28:51,461
(Pastor Kevin) Sure, I do.

523
00:28:51,531 --> 00:28:53,863
Actually,
we work with several area businesses

524
00:28:53,933 --> 00:28:57,027
to find entry-level jobs for our people.

525
00:28:57,103 --> 00:28:59,298
So I'm not the first
to come up with this idea?

526
