783
00:42:03,789 --> 00:42:05,188
isn't that wonderful?

784
00:42:05,258 --> 00:42:06,850
Wonderful? That's amazing.

785
00:42:06,926 --> 00:42:08,359
He needs you by his side.

786
00:42:08,427 --> 00:42:10,122
And who is this awful Uncle Frankie?

787
00:42:10,196 --> 00:42:12,858
Trust me, you don't want to meet him.

788
00:42:13,199 --> 00:42:17,226
- Amen.
- Amen.

789
00:42:17,303 --> 00:42:19,567
Thank you, Jesus.

790
00:42:19,839 --> 00:42:27,268
♪ I surrender all ♪

791
00:42:27,346 --> 00:42:36,744
♪ all to thee, my blessed Savior ♪

792
00:42:36,822 --> 00:42:44,558
♪ I surrender all ♪

793
00:43:00,546 --> 00:43:04,642
There's something
troubling that young man.

794
00:43:04,717 --> 00:43:06,241
Did you hear me?

795
00:43:06,319 --> 00:43:07,843
Hmm?

796
00:43:07,920 --> 00:43:11,720
That young man, Omar.

797
00:43:11,791 --> 00:43:14,726
Yeah?

798
00:43:14,794 --> 00:43:17,786
He's in some kind of trouble.

799
00:43:17,863 --> 00:43:21,355
I just don't know what it is.

800
00:43:21,434 --> 00:43:24,369
Well, he belongs to Jesus now.

801
00:43:27,573 --> 00:43:34,706
And that Lorenzo.
Are you listening to me?

802
00:43:34,780 --> 00:43:35,974
Yes, yes.

803
00:43:36,249 --> 00:43:38,274
I don't trust him.

804
00:43:38,351 --> 00:43:40,251
You don't trust who?

805
00:43:40,319 --> 00:43:42,810
Lorenzo.

806
00:43:44,957 --> 00:43:48,620
Well, Wanda, he's doing
a great service for us.

807
00:43:48,694 --> 00:43:51,663
Hmm, something tells me he's doing

808
00:43:51,731 --> 00:43:54,757
a great service for himself.

809
00:43:56,669 --> 00:44:01,606
♪♪♪

810
00:44:21,193 --> 00:44:24,492
No, no. Oh, dear.

811
00:44:24,563 --> 00:44:26,622
Oh, dear.

812
00:44:26,698 --> 00:44:29,496
I've been here for 2 years.
I just can't believe it.

813
00:44:29,568 --> 00:44:31,900
- How long have you been here?
- I've been here 5 years.

814
00:44:31,970 --> 00:44:34,803
Oh, help me.

815
00:44:35,707 --> 00:44:39,473
Well, Milly, we're all in the same boat.

816
00:44:39,544 --> 00:44:41,944
Don't take it so hard.

817
00:44:47,285 --> 00:44:49,446
(Lorenzo) Omar, I need to see you.

818
00:44:58,964 --> 00:45:01,296
- Well?
- Well, what?

819
00:45:01,366 --> 00:45:03,926
Well, what'd he say?

820
00:45:04,002 --> 00:45:06,334
Not much.

821
00:45:06,404 --> 00:45:09,271
I've been let go.

822
00:45:10,375 --> 00:45:12,843
He can't do that.

823
00:45:14,980 --> 00:45:17,505
According to my contract, he can.

824
00:45:17,582 --> 00:45:20,449
Yours too, I would imagine.

825
00:45:20,518 --> 00:45:24,386
Yeah, well, we'll see about that.

826
00:45:25,490 --> 00:45:30,427
♪♪♪

827
00:45:40,538 --> 00:45:43,871
(Lorenzo) Have a seat, Mr. Carmody.

828
00:45:43,942 --> 00:45:45,773
I don't know what kind of
stunt this is you're trying

829
00:45:45,844 --> 00:45:48,745
to pull, but I'm gonna put
a stop to it right now.

830
00:45:48,813 --> 00:45:50,337
Really?

831
00:45:50,415 --> 00:45:52,349
What do you think you're doing?

832
00:45:52,417 --> 00:45:55,409
Firing the entire staff in one day?

833
00:45:55,487 --> 00:45:57,250
It's not the entire staff, Mr. Carmody.

834
00:45:57,322 --> 00:45:58,584
Oh, no? Oh, okay.

835
00:45:58,657 --> 00:46:01,649
Well, who stays on besides you?

836
00:46:01,726 --> 00:46:03,455
That is confidential information,

837
00:46:03,528 --> 00:46:06,361
and you'll never draw it out of me.

838
00:46:06,431 --> 00:46:08,695
Wait 'til Stan hears about this.

839
00:46:08,767 --> 00:46:10,758
What you fail to realize, Mr. Carmody--

840
00:46:10,835 --> 00:46:13,929
Oh, come on, my name is Bob.

841
00:46:14,005 --> 00:46:16,997
All right, Bob.

842
00:46:17,075 --> 00:46:22,536
What you fail to realize is
that Mr. Davenport, Stan,

843
00:46:22,614 --> 00:46:27,847
does know about this and has
given it his complete approval.

844
00:46:27,919 --> 00:46:30,649
I don't believe it.

845
00:46:30,722 --> 00:46:32,986
Stan has been unhappy with
most everyone's performance

846
00:46:33,058 --> 00:46:35,288
around here for a long time.

847
00:46:35,360 --> 00:46:38,386
The numbers are simply not adding up.

848
00:46:38,463 --> 00:46:40,954
The numbers? What numbers?

849
00:46:41,032 --> 00:46:43,330
(Lorenzo) The numbers, Bob.

850
00:46:43,401 --> 00:46:45,369
Why do you think he's gone
away for who knows how long?

851
00:46:45,437 --> 00:46:47,405
He's taking a vacation, that's why.

852
00:46:47,472 --> 00:46:50,566
Au contraire, Bob. He's cleaning house.

853
00:46:50,642 --> 00:46:53,008
Getting rid of the deadwood,
the barnacles

854
00:46:53,078 --> 00:46:54,636
on the hull of the ship.

855
00:46:54,713 --> 00:46:56,010
And guess what?

856
00:46:56,081 --> 00:46:57,708
He's left me to do the dirty work.

857
00:46:57,782 --> 00:46:58,874
Why?

858
00:46:58,950 --> 00:47:01,043
Because he fears confrontation.

859
00:47:01,119 --> 00:47:05,783
Doesn't know how to call
a spade a spade, and I do.

860
00:47:07,092 --> 00:47:08,923
♪♪♪

861
00:47:08,993 --> 00:47:10,324
(Lorenzo) What are you doing?

862
00:47:10,395 --> 00:47:11,623
I'm calling Stan, right now.

863
00:47:11,696 --> 00:47:13,789
You know he's incommunicado?

864
00:47:13,865 --> 00:47:14,832
Oh, yeah?

865
00:47:14,899 --> 00:47:16,628
Well, I happen to have
his private cell phone number

866
00:47:16,701 --> 00:47:17,827
right here.

867
00:47:17,902 --> 00:47:19,699
We'll see about this.

868
00:47:19,771 --> 00:47:22,467
If I were you, I'd sue him.

869
00:47:22,540 --> 00:47:23,734
Sue him?

870
00:47:23,808 --> 00:47:25,469
(Lorenzo) Take him to the cleaners,
you got rights.

871
00:47:25,543 --> 00:47:26,771
You bet I do.

872
00:47:26,845 --> 00:47:27,971
He can't do this to you.

873
00:47:28,046 --> 00:47:29,741
I'm gonna fix you, Lorenzo Adams.

874
00:47:29,814 --> 00:47:31,111
Come on. Just let it out.

875
00:47:31,383 --> 00:47:33,010
I don't trust you, and I never did.

876
00:47:33,084 --> 00:47:35,518
Just get--vent all
that rage and hostility.

877
00:47:35,587 --> 00:47:37,714
Yeah, don't sweet talk me.

878
00:47:37,789 --> 00:47:39,484
(Lorenzo)
You think I like doing this, Bob?

879
00:47:39,557 --> 00:47:41,821
You think I like letting
Maude and Milly go

880
00:47:41,893 --> 00:47:44,589
or putting jaded Johnny
out on the street?

881
00:47:44,662 --> 00:47:46,823
Of course not.

882
00:47:57,709 --> 00:48:01,076
Stan's private cell phone,
may I help you?

883
00:48:04,749 --> 00:48:07,946
Omar, would you please
escort Mr. Carmody out?

884
00:48:08,019 --> 00:48:10,954
Thank you. Bye-bye.

885
00:48:20,899 --> 00:48:22,423
No.

886
00:48:22,500 --> 00:48:24,661
No, I'm not gonna let
him get away with this.

887
00:48:24,736 --> 00:48:27,398
Lorenzo-- get your hands off me.

888
00:48:27,472 --> 00:48:29,099
What are you doing? Knock it off!

889
00:48:29,174 --> 00:48:31,938
- Oh!
- Oh!

890
00:48:32,010 --> 00:48:34,444
[falling down stairs] Boom! Boom! Boom!

891
00:48:34,512 --> 00:48:35,877
Ah!

892
00:48:35,947 --> 00:48:38,415
Oh.

893
00:48:38,483 --> 00:48:40,576
Ah.

894
00:48:40,652 --> 00:48:42,620
Oh.

895
00:48:42,687 --> 00:48:45,087
(Lorenzo) I know this is a shock
for everyone, but please,

896
00:48:45,156 --> 00:48:46,987
we really need to try
and handle ourselves

897
00:48:47,058 --> 00:48:50,152
in a more professional manner, okay?

898
00:48:50,228 --> 00:48:52,594
Now finish clearing out your desks

899
00:48:52,664 --> 00:48:57,829
and come back in 2 weeks
for your final pay checks.

900
00:48:57,902 --> 00:48:59,961
That is all.

901
00:49:02,240 --> 00:49:05,175
(Bob) Milly. Milly.

902
00:49:06,811 --> 00:49:09,177
Iggy, come into my office.

903
00:49:11,816 --> 00:49:13,545
Iggy.

904
00:49:13,618 --> 00:49:17,918
Watch your-- Move my arm.

905
00:49:17,989 --> 00:49:22,085
Iggy, where you going, Iggy?

906
00:49:22,160 --> 00:49:24,492
I'm sorry, Bob.

907
00:49:24,562 --> 00:49:26,496
(Bob) Iggy.

908
00:49:28,032 --> 00:49:30,694
(female)
Don't move. Can you move your head?

909
00:49:30,768 --> 00:49:32,702
(Bob) It hurts.

910
00:49:33,410 --> 00:49:35,344
(Lorenzo)
So anyway, today at the agency,

911
00:49:35,412 --> 00:49:37,243
we set all kinds of records.

912
00:49:37,314 --> 00:49:38,838
It was an unbelievable day.

913
00:49:38,915 --> 00:49:41,475
You're not--hey, what
do you got there, big guy?

914
00:49:41,551 --> 00:49:42,984
One of your favorites.

915
00:49:43,053 --> 00:49:44,987
Fettuccine alfredo!

916
00:49:45,055 --> 00:49:46,682
Yummy.

917
00:49:46,757 --> 00:49:48,884
You're gonna love this.

918
00:49:48,959 --> 00:49:55,364
Cilantro and other special
ingredients, only known to me.

919
00:49:55,432 --> 00:49:56,763
You're the best, Omar.

920
00:49:56,833 --> 00:49:58,596
Yes.

921
00:49:58,669 --> 00:50:03,299
Nope, down. Good.

922
00:50:03,373 --> 00:50:06,308
Give me your hands.

923
00:50:12,082 --> 00:50:16,018
God, thank you for the food.

924
00:50:16,086 --> 00:50:22,958
Help Lorenzo get the money
that he needs.

925
00:50:23,026 --> 00:50:25,586
In Jesus' name, Amen.

926
00:50:27,497 --> 00:50:32,402
Hey, can I have some of that?

927
00:50:32,402 --> 00:50:35,701
Welcome to your first day
on the job, folks.

928
00:50:35,772 --> 00:50:39,401
This handsome gentleman right
here is Ignatius Pendergas

929
00:50:39,476 --> 00:50:41,740
or Iggy for short.

930
00:50:41,812 --> 00:50:43,575
He'll be walking you through
the day today, helping you

931
00:50:43,647 --> 00:50:45,979
with the ins and outs of
the computer software

932
00:50:46,049 --> 00:50:49,416
and telephone scripts
you'll need to memorize.

933
00:50:49,486 --> 00:50:53,786
Over here is Omar Adams, my nephew.

934
00:50:53,857 --> 00:50:55,688
Just returned from another tour of duty

935
00:50:55,759 --> 00:50:59,593
with the U.S. Army, learning
to reintegrate into society

936
00:50:59,663 --> 00:51:03,622
after experiencing fierce
battles involving

937
00:51:03,700 --> 00:51:10,936
vicious hand-to-hand combat
and not a few fatalities.

938
00:51:11,007 --> 00:51:13,999
Don't mess with him.

939
00:51:14,077 --> 00:51:19,014
I'm Lorenzo Adams.
I guess you know that by now.

940
00:51:19,082 --> 00:51:23,917
And I'll be directing operations
from my command post over there.

941
00:51:24,955 --> 00:51:27,947
Now, let's be clear
about something, folks.

942
00:51:28,024 --> 00:51:31,357
This is, first and foremost, a business.

943
00:51:31,428 --> 00:51:35,660
Sometimes business is rough.
Sometimes business is hardball.

944
00:51:35,732 --> 00:51:37,962
Collections can truly be
a classic struggle

945
00:51:38,034 --> 00:51:40,764
between the forces of good and evil.

946
00:51:40,837 --> 00:51:42,498
- Amen.
- Amen, sister.

947
00:51:42,572 --> 00:51:45,473
Shout for glory because
with God on our side,

948
00:51:45,542 --> 00:51:48,841
we will prevail over Ramoth-gilead.

949
00:51:48,912 --> 00:51:52,473
Now sure, we can all relate to
the poor schmoe who gets himself

950
00:51:52,549 --> 00:51:53,880
into a financeable bind.

951
00:51:53,950 --> 00:51:56,418
But, people,
we're here to collect money.

952
00:51:56,486 --> 00:51:58,784
I'll say that again, collect money,

953
00:51:58,855 --> 00:52:00,152
collect hard, collect fast.

954
00:52:00,424 --> 00:52:01,686
Never give up. Never give in.

955
00:52:01,758 --> 00:52:04,886
And think about it, you're
doing your company a service.

956
00:52:04,961 --> 00:52:07,521
You're doing your nation's
economy a service.

957
00:52:07,597 --> 00:52:09,462
You're doing your family a service.

958
00:52:09,533 --> 00:52:11,558
You're even helping the poor
schmoe who owes money

959
00:52:11,635 --> 00:52:13,569
in the first place
'cause at the end of the day,

960
00:52:13,637 --> 00:52:16,504
you're helping him get
the monkey of debt off his back.

961
00:52:16,573 --> 00:52:18,541
Ha-ha-ha-ha!

962
00:52:18,608 --> 00:52:22,544
Ah! I--I love this job.

963
00:52:22,612 --> 00:52:25,843
Okay, let's go over how this works.

964
00:52:25,916 --> 00:52:29,113
Iggy, I need your help here
on the bridge.

965
00:52:29,186 --> 00:52:35,489
Now debtor X originally owed
$1,200 after medicaid paid

966
00:52:35,559 --> 00:52:37,049
its portion of the bill.

967
00:52:37,127 --> 00:52:40,585
Debtor X has successfully
resisted all efforts

968
00:52:40,664 --> 00:52:43,400
by the hospital to collect
on the amount due.

969
00:52:43,628 --> 00:52:47,655
Enter Lump Sum Collection
Agency along with

970
00:52:47,732 --> 00:52:51,566
the rising stars of the LEC.

971
00:52:51,636 --> 00:52:54,901
For the next 2 weeks only,
we're gonna offer debtor X

972
00:52:54,972 --> 00:52:58,408
the opportunity of satisfying
his debt for only pennies

973
00:52:58,476 --> 00:52:59,943
on the dollar.

974
00:53:00,011 --> 00:53:01,069
That's right.

975
00:53:01,346 --> 00:53:03,371
We're gonna offer debtor X
the opportunity of satisfying

976
00:53:03,448 --> 00:53:06,315
his debt for only 40 cents
on the dollar,

977
00:53:06,384 --> 00:53:10,787
or in this case, $480 instead of $1,200.

978
00:53:10,855 --> 00:53:13,983
And very important,
if debtor X actually comes

979
00:53:14,058 --> 00:53:16,322
into the office and pays in cash,

980
00:53:16,394 --> 00:53:20,797
we're gonna take an additional 10% off!

981
00:53:20,865 --> 00:53:25,097
Any questions? Good.

982
00:53:25,370 --> 00:53:26,962
Let's weigh anchor, Iggy.

983
00:53:27,038 --> 00:53:29,472
Let's get started.

984
00:53:36,781 --> 00:53:41,445
Kasheera, can I see you in
my office here just a second?

985
00:53:44,422 --> 00:53:46,686
What did I do now?

986
00:53:49,527 --> 00:53:51,051
Come on in here. Have a seat.

987
00:53:51,129 --> 00:53:53,029
Have a seat.

988
00:53:53,097 --> 00:53:54,928
I need you to take dictation.

989
00:53:54,999 --> 00:53:56,626
I've never done that before,
Mr. Lorenzo.

990
00:53:56,701 --> 00:53:58,430
Don't worry, I'll show you the ropes.

991
00:53:58,503 --> 00:54:02,599
Okay.

992
00:54:02,673 --> 00:54:05,733
Ah! Ah, ah, oh.

993
00:54:05,810 --> 00:54:06,970
You all right, Mr. Lorenzo?

994
00:54:07,044 --> 00:54:08,807
No, a football injury, never mind.

995
00:54:08,880 --> 00:54:09,642
I just need to lay down.

996
00:54:09,714 --> 00:54:12,649
Okay.

997
00:54:12,717 --> 00:54:14,582
Mr. Lorenzo.

998
00:54:14,652 --> 00:54:17,780
All right, just right here.
I'm gonna just lay down.

999
00:54:17,855 --> 00:54:19,117
Go ahead. Go ahead.

1000
00:54:19,190 --> 00:54:20,418
Have a seat.

1001
00:54:20,491 --> 00:54:23,392
Can you just help me
put my feet up there?

1002
00:54:23,461 --> 00:54:27,727
Oh, yeah, that's better.

1003
00:54:27,799 --> 00:54:29,892
Now, where was I?

1004
00:54:29,967 --> 00:54:31,491
You wanted me to take dictation.

1005
00:54:31,569 --> 00:54:32,729
(Lorenzo) I remember now.

1006
00:54:32,804 --> 00:54:34,066
Should I go get my writing pad?

1007
00:54:34,138 --> 00:54:36,572
Maybe later.

1008
00:54:36,641 --> 00:54:38,040
- Boss!
- What?

1009
00:54:38,109 --> 00:54:39,133
We got a problem!

1010
00:54:39,210 --> 00:54:41,508
I thought I hired you
to handle problems!

1011
00:54:41,579 --> 00:54:44,707
(Iggy) Some of these people,
they can't even read.

1012
00:54:44,782 --> 00:54:47,683
Oh, I can't believe that.

1013
00:54:47,752 --> 00:54:53,782
Oh, oh, oh, oh.

1014
00:54:53,858 --> 00:54:56,190
Thanks.

1015
00:54:56,461 --> 00:54:58,622
The dictation can wait.

1016
00:54:58,696 --> 00:55:00,163
Yes, sir.

1017
00:55:00,231 --> 00:55:01,698
Go help Iggy.

1018
00:55:01,766 --> 00:55:03,666
We need a crash course
for everyone who can't read.

1019
00:55:03,734 --> 00:55:06,897
The basics and get the
professor on it right away.

1020
00:55:06,971 --> 00:55:08,836
He used to be a teacher.

1021
00:55:08,906 --> 00:55:10,874
And see who's got a good memory.

1022
00:55:10,942 --> 00:55:15,470
Maybe they can't read, but
they can memorize the script.

1023
00:55:15,546 --> 00:55:17,673
Oh, man.

1024
00:55:18,683 --> 00:55:23,620
♪♪♪

1025
00:55:30,928 --> 00:55:31,860
(Pastor Kevin) LEC.

1026
00:55:31,929 --> 00:55:33,556
- Pastor Kevin?
- Yes.

1027
00:55:33,631 --> 00:55:34,757
Lorenzo Adams here.

1028
00:55:34,832 --> 00:55:37,096
(Pastor Kevin)
Hello, Lorenzo. How are you?

1029
00:55:37,168 --> 00:55:41,002
Yeah, say, do you have
any volunteers who help

1030
00:55:41,072 --> 00:55:42,562
with literacy training?

1031
00:55:42,640 --> 00:55:43,971
(Pastor Kevin)
Yeah, yeah, we have a few.

1032
00:55:44,041 --> 00:55:46,134
Good, good. Send them over.

1033
00:55:46,210 --> 00:55:47,802
- All right.
- Thanks.

1034
00:55:47,879 --> 00:55:49,813
How are things going?

1035
00:55:50,686 --> 00:55:52,517
♪ I remember the day when I was lost ♪

1036
00:55:52,588 --> 00:55:53,919
♪ in a world of mistakes ♪

1037
00:55:53,989 --> 00:55:56,981
♪ Nowhere to run, I had no escape ♪

1038
00:55:57,059 --> 00:56:02,053
