1236
01:09:47,928 --> 01:09:50,954
Great, great. Where are you?

1237
01:09:51,031 --> 01:09:53,124
(Stan) I took a boat over
to Little Cayman this morning.

1238
01:09:53,200 --> 01:09:56,795
I was going stir crazy,
just had to call somebody.

1239
01:09:56,871 --> 01:09:57,963
How's Marcia?

1240
01:09:58,038 --> 01:10:00,006
(Stan) Oh, she's fine. Everyone's fine.

1241
01:10:00,074 --> 01:10:02,201
In fact,
we're coming home a few days early.

1242
01:10:02,276 --> 01:10:04,574
- No!
- What's that?

1243
01:10:04,645 --> 01:10:06,909
No kidding, boss.

1244
01:10:06,981 --> 01:10:09,506
That's terrific.

1245
01:10:09,583 --> 01:10:11,744
I am so happy for you.

1246
01:10:11,819 --> 01:10:13,047
(Stan) Thanks.

1247
01:10:13,120 --> 01:10:14,610
How are the hospital collections coming?

1248
01:10:14,688 --> 01:10:16,747
Oh, fantastic.

1249
01:10:16,824 --> 01:10:19,850
You--you wouldn't believe
how good it's going.

1250
01:10:19,927 --> 01:10:23,090
It's really-- it's hard to believe.

1251
01:10:23,163 --> 01:10:25,723
(Stan) That good, huh?

1252
01:10:25,799 --> 01:10:28,666
Oh, boss. Oh boss, yeah.

1253
01:10:28,736 --> 01:10:30,533
Yeah, it's really something.

1254
01:10:30,604 --> 01:10:32,731
We're working on it day and night.

1255
01:10:32,806 --> 01:10:35,206
(Stan) Day and night? Go Lorenzo.

1256
01:10:35,276 --> 01:10:37,244
What's Bob have to say about that?

1257
01:10:37,311 --> 01:10:38,676
Bob?

1258
01:10:38,746 --> 01:10:40,611
(Stan) Yeah, he's always
complaining about something or other.

1259
01:10:40,681 --> 01:10:42,581
Oh, yeah, Bob.

1260
01:10:42,650 --> 01:10:44,242
Well, you know Bob.

1261
01:10:44,318 --> 01:10:48,812
He's--I'll tell you all
about it when I see ya.

1262
01:10:48,889 --> 01:10:50,789
(Stan) Great, see ya on Friday.

1263
01:10:50,858 --> 01:10:52,519
No, I need more time!

1264
01:10:52,593 --> 01:10:55,926
(Stan) More time for what?

1265
01:10:55,996 --> 01:10:59,295
What, Stan? I can't hear you.

1266
01:10:59,567 --> 01:11:05,563
I was saying, Marcia needs
all the time you can give her.

1267
01:11:05,639 --> 01:11:07,971
(Stan) Yeah, you're right.

1268
01:11:08,042 --> 01:11:09,669
I'll see ya on Monday then.

1269
01:11:09,743 --> 01:11:11,267
See ya then.

1270
01:11:11,345 --> 01:11:15,111
(Stan) Thanks, Lorenzo.
Thanks for everything.

1271
01:11:23,724 --> 01:11:25,555
Good morning.

1272
01:11:25,626 --> 01:11:28,117
Morning.

1273
01:11:28,195 --> 01:11:31,255
Ah, thank you.

1274
01:11:34,635 --> 01:11:36,694
I needed that.

1275
01:11:36,770 --> 01:11:39,238
Oh, I need to see
the professor.

1276
01:11:39,306 --> 01:11:41,706
Yes, sir.

1277
01:12:06,425 --> 01:12:11,362
♪♪♪

1278
01:12:26,879 --> 01:12:30,076
I say all that to say
mission accomplished.

1279
01:12:30,149 --> 01:12:35,018
The hospital accounts are
settled, thanks to each of you.

1280
01:12:35,087 --> 01:12:40,354
And to show each of you my
appreciation, I'm gonna

1281
01:12:40,426 --> 01:12:45,056
give each one of you
one of these Lorenzo dolls.

1282
01:12:45,131 --> 01:12:47,463
Alas, poor Lorenzo.

1283
01:12:47,533 --> 01:12:51,094
I knew him, Iggy.

1284
01:12:51,170 --> 01:12:57,040
A man of--a man of.

1285
01:12:58,878 --> 01:13:03,008
"Alas, poor Yorick!

1286
01:13:03,082 --> 01:13:08,019
